The paper deals with computational complexity of graph modification problems, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories as they cover topics related to graph theory and computational complexity. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a likely category as it deals with algorithms and complexity related to geometric structures, which can be applied to graphs. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are also possible categories as they cover topics related to computational complexity and algorithms.
